description:
Two coordinated edits:

1. Wrap the module export at the flake level so it can see turnkey's own self.lib:

   # flake.nix
   flake.flakeModules.turnkey = import ./nix/flake-parts/turnkey {
     turnkeyLib = self.lib;
   };

2. Change nix/flake-parts/turnkey/default.nix signature to receive turnkeyLib:

   { turnkeyLib }:
   { lib, flake-parts-lib, ... }: { ... }

   And default the options:

     tellerLib = mkOption {
       type = types.anything;
       default = turnkeyLib.defaultTellerLib;
       defaultText = lib.literalExpression "inputs.turnkey.lib.defaultTellerLib";
       description = ''
         Teller library instance. Defaults to the teller flake input bundled
         with turnkey. Override only when using a non-default teller revision.
       '';
     };

     tellerRegistry = mkOption {
       type = types.lazyAttrsOf types.anything;
       default = turnkeyLib.defaultTellerRegistry system;
       defaultText = lib.literalExpression "inputs.turnkey.lib.defaultTellerRegistry system";
       description = ''
         Versioned registry. Defaults to the toolbox-backed registry bundled
         with turnkey. Override to point at a private registry overlay.
       '';
       # internal = true REMOVED — this is now a documented override point.
     };

Verify: turnkey's own devshells must still evaluate (the inlined block in turnkey's own consumer remains and explicitly overrides — collapsing that consumer happens in the next ticket).
